<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 17 Sept
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: National Bureau of Animal Health Epidemiology Bureau, Argentina
[edited]

Foot and mouth disease outbreak in Tartagal, province of Salta
--------------------------------------------------------------
Zoning report No 3: advance of sanitary actions, National Bureau of Animal
Health Epidemiology Bureau 11 Sep 2003
Zoning
------
The strategy established to mitigate the sanitary risk is the zoning of the
province of Salta, involving the departments of San Martin, Santa Victoria,
Oran, Iruya and Rivadavia, and the department of Ramon Lista in the
province of Formosa; these last 2 are currently interdicted due to the
sanitary aalert with Paraguay.
Characteristics of the zone
---------------------------
The zone has a surface of 65 327 sq km and 4320 producers, with regards to
livestock population, it is detailed in table 1.
Table 1: distribution of surface, farms and susceptible animals per department.
Department / surface Km / farms / bovines / porcines / ovines / caprines /
Susceptible Totals(*)
