(*) Total number of susceptible animals in the sanitary emergency zone 481 713
Advance report of the actions
-----------------------------
Biosecurity and disinfection measures are still being carried out at the
sacrifice area. The issuance of animal transit documents (DTA) is still
suspended for all movements in the departments included in the zoning, with
the exception of those intended for local immediate slaughter.
Entrance of animals to the zone is still prohibited, with the exception of
those intended for local immediate slaughter. The above mentioned
departments have been excluded from making export slaughter dispatches.
Municipal slaughterhouses in Tartagal, Aguaray, and Salvador Mazza, all of
them in the department of San Mart√≠n, province of Salta, are still closed.
Within the emergency zone, the focal areas (affected farm), perifocal area
zone of 3 kms from the outbreak, and surveillance area (zone of 10 kms
outside the perifocal area) have been established. 4 control and
disinfection posts have been established.
Confiscations:
33 bovines, sent to sanitary slaughter.
5 ovines, 4 caprines and 11 porcines, sacrifice and incineration.
Report of Stocks and Implemented Actions:
The following is the description of the number of livestock at the affected
area (focal, perifocal, and surveillance), and the sanitary actions carried
out to date:
Focal area / producers / bovines / ovines and caprines / porcines / total
Existences* / 10 / 3 / 12 / 58 / 73
Vaccinations / -- / -- / -- / -- / --
Serological samples / 4 / 31 / -- / 48 /--
Sacrifice* / -- / 3 / 12 / 58 /73
*In addition to serum samples, esophagus pharyngeal liquid was collected
from these 3 bovines for Probang test.
** The focal area animals (37 pigs) and their contacts are added to the
existences. Sacrifice and incineration of these animals was completed.
Serum samples for complementary analysis were collected, and LEF was
removed from 2 bovines, in addition to the organs (pharyngeal wall and
tonsils) removed from one of them for viral isolation.
